            "preview": "14  Virtues of the Holy Qur'an \t For a lover, the moments of greatest pleasure are those  when, in the presence of his beloved, he is full of self-  r...",
            "content": "<div class=\"story-content\"><p>14 <br>Virtues of the Holy Qur'an \t<br>For a lover, the moments of greatest pleasure are those <br>when, in the presence of his beloved, he is full of self- <br>reproach and shedding tears profusely. <br>One should not read fast unless one desires to memor- <br>I <br>ize it. The Qu'ran should be placed in a slightly elevated <br>position on a wooden stand or a pillow. One should not <br>talk to others during recitation. If one is forced by necessity <br>to speak to someone, it should be done after first closing <br>the Book, and then recite 'Ta'awwudh' (seeking refuge of <br>Allah against Satan), before reading again. If people nearby <br>are occupied in their work, reading in a low voice is appre- <br>ciated otherwise reading loudly is more rewarding. <br>The Masha'ikh have mentioned six external and six in- <br>ternal rules of reverence for reading the Holy Qu'ran, <br>which are given below: <br>I <br>Rules of External Iieverence <br>(1) Perform Wudhu and then sit facing Qiblah in an <br>extremely dignified manner. <br>(2) \t Do not proceed fast, but read with measure and <br>correct pronunciation. <br>(3) \t Try to weep, even if vou have to compel yourself <br>to do so. <br>(4) \t The response to ayaat of mercy or 01 punishment<br>should be as explained above. <br>(5) \t Reading should be in a low vo~ce. if insincerity is <br>apprehended on your own part or disturbance is <br>caused to others. Otherwise read in a loud voice. <br>(6) Read in a melodious voice, because there are nu- \t<br>v <br>merous ahadith laying emphasis on this. <br>Rules oflnternal Reverence <br>(1) The heart should be full of the glory of Qur'an i.e. <br>realizing how sublime it is. <br>(2) \t Bear in the heart the Loftiness, Majesty and Mag- <br>nificence of Almighty Allah, Whose Revelation the <br>Qu'ran is.</p></div>"
